Title: On the holographic duals of N=1 gauge dynamics
Authors: J. Sonnenschein, A. Loewy
Comments: 25 pages, latex, v2: references added, typos corrected, section 6
  revised
Report-no: TAUP-2658-01
Journal-ref: JHEP 0108 (2001) 007
\\
  We analyze the holographic description of several properties of $\N=1$
confining gauge dynamics. In particular we discuss Wilson loops including the
issues of a Luscher term and the broadening of the flux tubes, 't Hooft loops,
baryons, instantons, chiral symmetry breaking, the gluino condensate and BPS
domain walls.
